The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                              NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Feb. 10 (PTI): The Supreme Court has said that in a case based on circumstantial evidence, the fact that the accused had gone to the victims house armed with deadly weapons was sufficient to convict them of murder.           
	The ruling came on a petition by convicts Balwant Singh, Harbans Singh, Malkiat Singh and Balwinder Singh, all from Bhatinda in Punjab, seeking acquittal in a murder case on the ground that there was no direct evidence against them.                  
	Ghaziabad (PTI): A five-year-old boy who was playing with his fathers revolver accidentally pulled the trigger and critically injured his eight-year-old sister. The parents were not at home and the revolver was lying on a table, police said.                  
	Moga (PTI): Moga district police have arrested three persons who illegally filled LPG cylinders at a workshop and sold them in the black market. The police are looking for a fourth member of the gang.                  
	Rameshwaram (PTI): A fisherman from Tamil Nadu was killed when the Sri Lankan navy fired at his boat in the Palk Strait, officials said on Sunday. Thangapandi, 35, had put out to sea off the Dhanushkodi coast with two other fishermen, Idumban and Babu.                  
	Jammu (PTI): Actress Sushmita Sen visited the holy cave shrine of Vaishnodevi on Sunday and offered prayers. She later left for Delhi, sources said. Last week, actress Preity Zinta visited the shrine in Jammu and Kashmirs Reasi district.                   
	 Rajkot (PTI): Two persons died of cold in Saurashtra on Saturday and Sunday. A weeklong cold wave has disrupted life in Saurashtra and Kutch in western Gujarat.                                                                                                                           
